cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with the detection of driver behavior from naturalistic driving recordings, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with robotics (RO) as it involves the detection of driver behavior for autonomous vehicles. The use of self-supervised and supervised learning techniques also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.AI. Finally, the fusion of multimodal cues suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM.
